about.summary: Routines for simple graphs and network analysis. It can handle large graphs very well and provides functions for generating random and regular graphs, graph visualization, centrality methods and much more.

name: r-igraph
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.2.6" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-igraph
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/igraph_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/igraph/igraph_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 640da72166fda84bea2c0e5eee374f1ed80cd9439c1171d056b1b1737ae6c76d

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}  # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}grep              # [win]
    - {{ posix }}autoconf
    - {{ posix }}automake          # [not win]
    - {{ posix }}automake-wrapper  # [win]
    - {{ posix }}pkg-config
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-matrix                     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-magrittr                   # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-pkgconfig >=2.0.0          # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - libblas
    - liblapack
    - gmp  # [not win]
    - libxml2
    - r-matrix
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pkgconfig >=2.0.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - gmp  # [not win]
    - libxml2
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-matrix
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pkgconfig >=2.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('igraph')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('igraph')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://igraph.org
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Routines for simple graphs and network analysis. It can handle large graphs very well and provides functions for generating random and regular graphs, graph visualization, centrality methods and much more.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
